WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.112 --> 00:00:05.642
THE HUSBAND

2
00:00:06.168 --> 00:00:07.184
PRODUCTION SUPPORTED BY:
KOREA COMMUNICATIONS DEVELOPMENT FUND.

3
00:00:07.208 --> 00:00:08.155
KOREA MEDIA AND COMMUNICATIONS COMMISSION.

4
00:00:08.179 --> 00:00:09.285
KOREA COMMUNICATIONS AGENCY

5
00:00:09.977 --> 00:00:11.103
THIS SERIES IS FICTITIOUS

6
00:00:11.183 --> 00:00:13.238
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED IN SELECT SCENES

7
00:00:14.741 --> 00:00:16.658
EPISODE 4

8
00:00:16.659 --> 00:00:18.744
[lock beeping]

9
00:00:18.745 --> 00:00:21.164
[door opens]

10
00:00:35.136 --> 00:00:36.304
You're home.

11
00:00:38.848 --> 00:00:40.642
Where were you all night?

12
00:00:41.643 --> 00:00:42.936
Why are you out here?

13
00:00:43.561 --> 00:00:44.854
You should be in bed.

14
00:00:46.564 --> 00:00:48.108
You've been acting weird lately.

15
00:00:48.608 --> 00:00:50.652
You're always late.
and I can never reach you.

16
00:00:55.115 --> 00:00:56.157
Something came up.

17
00:00:57.158 --> 00:00:59.327
[sighs] You couldn't even call me?

18
00:01:07.460 --> 00:01:08.461
Where's Hayun?

19
00:01:10.839 --> 00:01:14.217
She kept asking for you
then fell asleep a while ago.

20
00:01:15.385 --> 00:01:16.386
Right.

21
00:01:21.307 --> 00:01:23.101
What could possibly keep you out so late?

22
00:01:26.271 --> 00:01:28.898
I told you.
something came up at the hospital.

23
00:01:29.482 --> 00:01:30.650
[Seyun sighs]

24
00:01:33.403 --> 00:01:34.529
Honey.

25
00:01:36.072 --> 00:01:37.574
Are you hiding something from me?

26
00:01:40.618 --> 00:01:41.786
I'm not.

27
00:01:45.039 --> 00:01:46.749
You sure there's nothing going on?

28
00:01:49.961 --> 00:01:50.962
I'm sure.

29
00:01:53.381 --> 00:01:54.716
Fine.

30
00:01:57.844 --> 00:01:59.095
Listen.

31
00:02:00.096 --> 00:02:01.264
I'm your wife.

32
00:02:02.849 --> 00:02:06.644
You have to tell me
if there is something going on.

33
00:02:07.312 --> 00:02:11.148
I can tell you're having a hard time.
but you won't say anything.

34
00:02:11.149 --> 00:02:13.443
[♪ tender music playing]

35
00:02:16.279 --> 00:02:17.280
[sighs]

36
00:02:18.656 --> 00:02:19.657
Okay.

37
00:02:20.825 --> 00:02:23.620
I just hope
there's really nothing going on.

38
00:02:28.625 --> 00:02:30.126
But can I just say something?

39
00:02:30.710 --> 00:02:32.420
You've changed so much.

40
00:02:34.047 --> 00:02:36.049
I barely recognize you anymore.

41
00:02:48.144 --> 00:02:49.604
Where's your wedding ring?

42
00:02:51.856 --> 00:02:54.943
I took it off before surgery.
I probably left it in the office.

43
00:03:01.616 --> 00:03:03.618
- [♪ music stops]
- [siren blaring]

44
00:03:06.746 --> 00:03:09.248
[♪ dramatic music playing]

45
00:03:16.435 --> 00:03:18.561
ACCESS RESTRICTED

46
00:03:18.562 --> 00:03:19.938
ACCESS GRANTED

47
00:03:19.939 --> 00:03:24.527
RESTRICTED ACCESS
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

48
00:03:54.932 --> 00:03:56.599
[♪ music stops]

49
00:03:56.600 --> 00:03:57.601
Geez. you scared me.

50
00:03:58.019 --> 00:03:59.519
What are you doing here so late?

51
00:03:59.520 --> 00:04:01.604
You know.
I just left something in the office.

52
00:04:01.605 --> 00:04:04.733
[chuckles] Must be pretty damn important.

53
00:04:04.734 --> 00:04:06.526
Hang in there. then. See you.

54
00:04:06.527 --> 00:04:07.528
Okay.

55
00:04:09.113 --> 00:04:10.114
Chiung.

56
00:04:11.198 --> 00:04:12.282
Yes?

57
00:04:12.283 --> 00:04:14.160
What? You got something to say?

58
00:04:14.952 --> 00:04:16.911
- The thing is…
- [phone chiming]

59
00:04:16.912 --> 00:04:18.664
Sorry. let me take this real quick.

60
00:04:19.707 --> 00:04:20.915
This is Choi.

61
00:04:20.916 --> 00:04:23.626
[Dr. Ko] Dr. Choi. it's me.
I'll cut right to the chase.

62
00:04:23.627 --> 00:04:27.255
- Have you heard from Taeju at all?
- Yeah. what a coincidence.

63
00:04:27.256 --> 00:04:28.715
Are you with him right now?

64
00:04:28.716 --> 00:04:29.924
Yes.

65
00:04:29.925 --> 00:04:32.510
[Dr. Ko] The police are on their way.

66
00:04:32.511 --> 00:04:35.096
so you have to keep him there.
no matter what.

67
00:04:35.097 --> 00:04:36.557
Yeah. I got it.

68
00:04:37.433 --> 00:04:38.434
[groans]

69
00:04:41.228 --> 00:04:43.480
Chiung. I'm so sorry.

70
00:04:43.481 --> 00:04:44.981
I'll explain later!

71
00:04:44.982 --> 00:04:47.485
[♪ dramatic music resumes]

72
00:04:48.694 --> 00:04:49.779
[engine revs]

73
00:04:52.782 --> 00:04:54.908
RED LIGHT AND SPEEDING
SURVEILLANCE CAMERA

74
00:04:54.909 --> 00:04:56.785
[siren blaring]

75
00:04:56.786 --> 00:04:58.828
Captain. we got an update
on Kang's location.

76
00:04:58.829 --> 00:04:59.913
Where?

77
00:04:59.914 --> 00:05:03.041
He was at Deoksam Intersection
at 9:46 p.m.

78
00:05:03.042 --> 00:05:04.043
Heading that way.

79
00:05:14.678 --> 00:05:17.889
[officer 1]
Plate number 1228. please pull over.

80
00:05:17.890 --> 00:05:19.307
Pull over. 1228.

81
00:05:19.308 --> 00:05:20.434
[tires squeal]

82
00:05:21.018 --> 00:05:22.686
[horns honking]

83
00:05:24.230 --> 00:05:26.648
[officer 2] Suspect vehicle is heading
toward Shinyu-dong.

84
00:05:26.649 --> 00:05:28.859
Units two and three. in pursuit.

85
00:05:32.279 --> 00:05:33.280
[grunts. gasps]

86
00:05:35.950 --> 00:05:37.284
[Dosik] Kang Taeju!

87
00:05:37.785 --> 00:05:39.620
Pull over right now!

88
00:05:40.329 --> 00:05:41.913
Stop being so reckless!

89
00:05:41.914 --> 00:05:43.582
Cut him off! Get in front of him!

90
00:05:44.708 --> 00:05:46.335
Damn it.

91
00:05:51.465 --> 00:05:53.217
[tires screech]

92
00:05:55.219 --> 00:05:56.428
[♪ music stops]

93
00:05:56.429 --> 00:05:58.597
[tires squealing]

94
00:06:00.057 --> 00:06:02.560
[♪ dramatic music resumes]

95
00:06:04.895 --> 00:06:06.271
Turn around! Step on it!

96
00:06:06.272 --> 00:06:10.359
[officer 3] Control. we lost the suspect
vehicle during pursuit. Plate number 1228.

97
00:06:12.403 --> 00:06:15.322
[people gasping. exclaiming]

98
00:06:31.714 --> 00:06:33.632
- [♪ music stops]
- [Seyun yelps]

99
00:06:37.011 --> 00:06:38.929
[whimpers. pants]

100
00:06:42.600 --> 00:06:45.060
[gasps. panting]

101
00:06:52.109 --> 00:06:54.612
[♪ tense music playing]

102
00:07:14.340 --> 00:07:17.133
- [♪ music fades]
- [siren blaring]

103
00:07:17.134 --> 00:07:19.136
[horn honking]

104
00:07:23.849 --> 00:07:24.892
[siren stops]

105
00:07:25.643 --> 00:07:27.518
Everyone. back up!

106
00:07:27.519 --> 00:07:28.729
Keep them away!

107
00:07:37.571 --> 00:07:39.948
Captain. it looks like he went
toward the main road.

108
00:07:39.949 --> 00:07:41.867
Go after him. He couldn't have gone far.

109
00:07:46.288 --> 00:07:48.791
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

110
00:07:58.550 --> 00:08:00.302
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

111
00:08:13.816 --> 00:08:17.485
TAKING ACCOUNTABILITY
FOR THE PEOPLE

112
00:08:17.486 --> 00:08:20.239
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

113
00:08:34.545 --> 00:08:36.255
- [♪ music stops]
- [detective 1] Hey. stop!

114
00:08:38.716 --> 00:08:41.092
- [detective 2] Kang Taeju is over there!
- [detective 3] Back up!

115
00:08:41.093 --> 00:08:44.429
[detective 1]
We found Kang Taeju. He's over there!

116
00:08:44.430 --> 00:08:47.433
- [♪ dramatic music playing]
- [siren blaring]

117
00:08:50.728 --> 00:08:51.770
[tires screech]

118
00:08:52.896 --> 00:08:53.897
[Dosik] Go!

119
00:08:57.568 --> 00:08:58.902
- That way!
- [both] Yes. sir!

120
00:09:12.249 --> 00:09:13.625
[detective 1]
Get to the second floor. now!

121
00:09:13.626 --> 00:09:14.668
[detective 2] Yes. sir.

122
00:09:21.050 --> 00:09:22.425
Where did he go?

123
00:09:22.426 --> 00:09:24.678
Go the other way! Block him off!

124
00:09:29.975 --> 00:09:32.269
What the hell. man? Stop!

125
00:09:32.811 --> 00:09:34.729
[Dosik] What the hell are you doing?

126
00:09:34.730 --> 00:09:35.856
Get him!

127
00:09:36.815 --> 00:09:38.651
Hey! Wait. Kang Taeju!

128
00:09:44.323 --> 00:09:45.324
[grunts]

129
00:09:46.033 --> 00:09:47.492
- He's moving!
- That nutjob.

130
00:09:47.493 --> 00:09:49.202
Kang Taeju. stop!

131
00:09:49.203 --> 00:09:50.287
Kang Taeju!

132
00:09:50.829 --> 00:09:52.455
Chase him down!

133
00:09:52.456 --> 00:09:53.539
- Hey. Kim.
- Sir?

134
00:09:53.540 --> 00:09:55.709
- Request backup ASAP!
- Yes. sir.

135
00:09:58.170 --> 00:09:59.253
[♪ music stops]

136
00:09:59.254 --> 00:10:01.464
[officer]
Copy. Seongjin PD request for backup.

137
00:10:01.465 --> 00:10:03.549
Two patrol units rolling immediately.

138
00:10:03.550 --> 00:10:06.053
- Detective unit to follow.
- [sirens blaring]

139
00:10:23.487 --> 00:10:25.989
[♪ tense music playing]

140
00:10:31.203 --> 00:10:32.746
[clangs. rattles]

141
00:10:53.350 --> 00:10:55.518
[exhales deeply]

142
00:10:55.519 --> 00:10:58.021
[♪ music intensifies]

143
00:11:00.315 --> 00:11:01.692
Seyun.

144
00:11:08.907 --> 00:11:10.033
Let's put an end to this.

145
00:11:10.909 --> 00:11:11.910
What?

146
00:11:14.079 --> 00:11:15.205
I want a divorce.

147
00:11:18.333 --> 00:11:19.918
That bastard.

148
00:11:21.336 --> 00:11:22.379
[grunts]

149
00:11:23.756 --> 00:11:27.259
- [Seonja] My gosh! What was that?
- [panting]

150
00:11:43.484 --> 00:11:45.986
[♪ dramatic music playing]

151
00:11:52.201 --> 00:11:53.618
[Hyeonsu] Move!

152
00:11:53.619 --> 00:11:54.620
[Park] Over there!

153
00:11:57.790 --> 00:11:58.957
[detective] That way.

154
00:12:18.310 --> 00:12:19.978
[♪ music fades]

155
00:12:22.773 --> 00:12:23.941
There you are.

156
00:12:25.567 --> 00:12:27.653
[♪ intense music playing]

157
00:12:29.571 --> 00:12:30.905
[grunts]

158
00:12:30.906 --> 00:12:34.201
You think you can play games with cops?
You have the right to an attorney--

159
00:12:36.245 --> 00:12:37.578
[detective] No!

160
00:12:37.579 --> 00:12:38.580
[both groan]

161
00:12:43.961 --> 00:12:45.963
[panting]

162
00:12:49.299 --> 00:12:51.051
[♪ music fades]

163
00:12:51.677 --> 00:12:53.679
[grunting]

164
00:13:01.228 --> 00:13:02.563
[detective] No…

165
00:13:03.522 --> 00:13:05.440
[grunts. groans]

166
00:13:12.114 --> 00:13:13.365
Kang Taeju…

167
00:13:17.202 --> 00:13:18.704
You can't move your arms and legs?

168
00:13:20.163 --> 00:13:23.666
- Your spinal cord is damaged.
- [groaning]

169
00:13:23.667 --> 00:13:26.545
You'll damage your nerves permanently
if you try to move.

170
00:13:33.427 --> 00:13:34.885
[detective gasps]

171
00:13:34.886 --> 00:13:37.097
[panting]

172
00:13:48.191 --> 00:13:49.568
Don't move. okay?

173
00:13:50.444 --> 00:13:52.571
[groaning]

174
00:13:53.196 --> 00:13:54.197
[grunts]

175
00:14:00.412 --> 00:14:01.496
Hold on…

176
00:14:07.836 --> 00:14:08.920
There you go.

177
00:14:15.594 --> 00:14:16.637
[phone beeps]

178
00:14:18.305 --> 00:14:19.931
Hello. we need an ambulance.

179
00:14:20.932 --> 00:14:24.018
Yeah. I'm at Ilseo Supply Center.

180
00:14:24.019 --> 00:14:27.648
There's a patient with spinal cord damage
in the stairwell down to the basement.

181
00:14:28.732 --> 00:14:31.943
Yeah. he needs to get to a hospital. STAT.
So please hurry.

182
00:14:37.783 --> 00:14:40.285
[♪ dramatic music playing]

183
00:15:06.061 --> 00:15:10.982
THE HUSBAND

184
00:15:13.068 --> 00:15:14.069
[♪ music stops]

185
00:15:15.445 --> 00:15:18.114
EMERGENCY SERVICES

186
00:15:18.115 --> 00:15:20.826
- Hey. Kim. You all right?
- [Kim] Wait. hold on.

187
00:15:21.326 --> 00:15:23.829
Captain. Kang Taeju…

188
00:15:24.496 --> 00:15:25.996
He took my gun.

189
00:15:25.997 --> 00:15:27.249
Your gun?

190
00:15:27.874 --> 00:15:29.000
I'm sorry. sir.

191
00:15:30.919 --> 00:15:32.254
[sighs]

192
00:15:34.381 --> 00:15:37.133
All right.
Don't worry about that right now.

193
00:15:37.134 --> 00:15:38.802
Please take him to the hospital.

194
00:15:44.099 --> 00:15:46.559
Hey. will he be okay?

195
00:15:46.560 --> 00:15:49.311
Well. we can't be sure
until we get to the hospital.

196
00:15:49.312 --> 00:15:53.650
but thanks to the prompt first aid.
I think he'll be able to avoid the worst.

197
00:15:56.945 --> 00:15:58.029
First aid?

198
00:16:02.075 --> 00:16:03.659
Hey. put out an APB on Kang Taeju.

199
00:16:03.660 --> 00:16:04.661
- I'm on it.
- Yes. sir.

200
00:16:36.151 --> 00:16:39.154
[breathing heavily]

201
00:16:45.827 --> 00:16:47.829
[train horn sounding]

202
00:16:51.833 --> 00:16:57.506
EUMGOK. JUNSEONG

203
00:17:04.971 --> 00:17:07.808
[operator. on speakers]
The doors are closing.

204
00:17:08.558 --> 00:17:13.313
THIS TRAIN IS BOUND FOR JUNSEONG

205
00:17:38.839 --> 00:17:40.841
[footsteps approaching]

206
00:17:46.930 --> 00:17:49.432
[♪ mysterious music playing]

207
00:17:51.810 --> 00:17:53.895
[stranger] I'm impressed. Kang Taeju.

208
00:18:01.486 --> 00:18:03.280
You actually made it.

209
00:18:05.240 --> 00:18:06.658
Where's my wife right now?

210
00:18:08.118 --> 00:18:09.119
Come with me.

211
00:18:22.799 --> 00:18:24.801
[♪ music continues]

212
00:18:29.097 --> 00:18:33.268
NAMGANG LIVESTOCK DISTRIBUTION

213
00:19:23.902 --> 00:19:25.070
[Taeju] Where are we?

214
00:19:26.488 --> 00:19:29.531
- I thought we were going to find my wife.
- [♪ music fades]

215
00:19:29.532 --> 00:19:32.743
That's for you
to figure out from here on out.

216
00:19:32.744 --> 00:19:33.787
[Taeju] Excuse me?

217
00:19:36.248 --> 00:19:37.249
[exhales sharply]

218
00:19:38.458 --> 00:19:40.085
Is this some kind of joke?

219
00:19:41.544 --> 00:19:44.256
You said you knew
I didn't have my wife kidnapped.

220
00:19:45.340 --> 00:19:48.134
You said you'd help me find her.
So where is she right now?

221
00:19:54.307 --> 00:19:56.476
NEUROSURGEON KANG TAEJU

222
00:19:58.144 --> 00:20:00.146
SEYUN

223
00:20:04.943 --> 00:20:06.236
[Taeju breathes shakily]

224
00:20:08.238 --> 00:20:09.239
What the hell?

225
00:20:10.031 --> 00:20:11.574
Are you working with that bastard?

226
00:20:12.200 --> 00:20:13.368
Where is my wife?

227
00:20:15.453 --> 00:20:16.955
Answer me!

228
00:20:17.998 --> 00:20:19.082
I told you.

229
00:20:20.041 --> 00:20:21.917
It's up to you to figure it out now.

230
00:20:21.918 --> 00:20:22.961
What?

231
00:20:23.837 --> 00:20:25.087
Are you kidding me?

232
00:20:25.088 --> 00:20:27.256
Do you want to die right here?

233
00:20:27.257 --> 00:20:28.675
Where's Seyun?

234
00:20:31.970 --> 00:20:34.514
Where is Seyun? Where is she?

235
00:20:35.640 --> 00:20:37.517
Have you ever killed a person before?

236
00:20:38.852 --> 00:20:39.853
What?

237
00:20:40.770 --> 00:20:43.564
You must have had
your opportunities as a doctor.

238
00:20:43.565 --> 00:20:46.818
There's only a fine line
between saving a life and taking one.

239
00:20:48.570 --> 00:20:49.946
What the hell are you saying?

240
00:20:50.739 --> 00:20:54.743
How far will Kang Taeju go for his wife?

241
00:20:57.537 --> 00:20:59.748
Could he kill a person?

242
00:21:06.421 --> 00:21:09.507
[♪ ominous music playing]

243
00:21:24.689 --> 00:21:26.399
[Taeju groans. grunts]

244
00:21:28.818 --> 00:21:30.487
[coughs]

245
00:21:35.200 --> 00:21:36.201
Say hi.

246
00:21:37.243 --> 00:21:38.244
That's my wife.

247
00:21:38.912 --> 00:21:40.914
[panting]

248
00:21:42.374 --> 00:21:44.125
If you can't find the bastard soon.

249
00:21:45.460 --> 00:21:47.420
your wife will end up like her too.

250
00:21:51.216 --> 00:21:53.885
That's why you're going to be my bait.

251
00:21:55.470 --> 00:21:57.097
You get your wife back.

252
00:21:58.932 --> 00:22:00.350
and I get to kill the bastard.

253
00:22:03.603 --> 00:22:04.604
[scoffs]

254
00:22:06.439 --> 00:22:07.440
[chuckles]

255
00:22:09.150 --> 00:22:10.819
What. so that's your wife?

256
00:22:14.864 --> 00:22:16.116
What does that even…

257
00:22:17.534 --> 00:22:18.535
[chuckles]

258
00:22:22.122 --> 00:22:23.747
PARK GYEONGMIN (FEMALE/30S)

259
00:22:23.748 --> 00:22:25.291
OCCUPATION
PHOTOGRAPHY INSTRUCTOR

260
00:22:29.504 --> 00:22:30.839
- [♪ music stops]
- [grunts]

261
00:22:32.298 --> 00:22:34.801
[♪ dramatic music playing]

262
00:22:39.514 --> 00:22:40.515
[gasps]

263
00:22:42.100 --> 00:22:44.102
[panting]

264
00:22:45.645 --> 00:22:46.938
You know. you're right.

265
00:22:48.314 --> 00:22:50.817
There's a fine line
between saving a life and taking one.

266
00:22:52.277 --> 00:22:53.695
That's the trade I'm in.

267
00:22:54.988 --> 00:22:56.739
It demands absolute precision.

268
00:22:57.824 --> 00:23:01.494
A tenth of a millimeter can
either kill or save a person.

269
00:23:02.036 --> 00:23:04.497
One nick to the brain stem
and they're dead on the table.

270
00:23:07.792 --> 00:23:09.209
Catch the spinal nerve root.

271
00:23:09.210 --> 00:23:13.923
and they're looking at
a lifetime of intractable. burning pain.

272
00:23:17.051 --> 00:23:18.261
Look. man.

273
00:23:21.264 --> 00:23:25.309
I don't care who's in that picture.
whether it's your wife or not.

274
00:23:25.310 --> 00:23:26.936
I only care about one thing.

275
00:23:29.898 --> 00:23:31.441
Where's my wife?

276
00:23:34.444 --> 00:23:36.446
- [door bangs]
- [♪ music stops]

277
00:23:51.836 --> 00:23:54.964
[Seonja exclaims] What was that?

278
00:23:55.882 --> 00:23:57.884
What on earth is going on?

279
00:24:14.317 --> 00:24:16.818
[door creaking]

280
00:24:16.819 --> 00:24:19.322
[♪ tense music playing]

281
00:24:56.985 --> 00:24:57.986
Hello?

282
00:24:58.987 --> 00:25:00.320
Hello? Are you in here?

283
00:25:00.321 --> 00:25:03.156
[Seonja exclaims] How did you get out?

284
00:25:03.157 --> 00:25:05.285
No time to explain.
We have to get out of here.

285
00:25:06.119 --> 00:25:07.120
[lock clanks]

286
00:25:12.041 --> 00:25:13.709
Why won't this thing open?

287
00:25:13.710 --> 00:25:16.004
- [Seonja] What? It won't open?
- No. it's…

288
00:25:17.880 --> 00:25:19.923
I think I'll need the keys to this door.

289
00:25:19.924 --> 00:25:21.758
[Seonja] Just save yourself while you can.

290
00:25:21.759 --> 00:25:23.970
No. I can't just leave you. Just hang on.

291
00:25:44.324 --> 00:25:45.783
I found the keys. Hold on.

292
00:25:46.409 --> 00:25:48.328
[Seonja] What? Really?

293
00:25:49.412 --> 00:25:50.538
Not this one.

294
00:25:52.332 --> 00:25:53.708
Come on.

295
00:25:54.542 --> 00:25:55.626
- Please.
- [Seonja] Oh. no.

296
00:25:55.627 --> 00:25:57.962
I don't think I stand a chance.

297
00:25:59.088 --> 00:26:01.841
Just get out of here.
You have to save yourself.

298
00:26:02.884 --> 00:26:06.054
Don't give up. You have to see
how your husband really feels.

299
00:26:16.648 --> 00:26:18.106
- [lock clicks]
- Got it.

300
00:26:18.107 --> 00:26:19.108
[thuds]

301
00:26:25.073 --> 00:26:27.575
[♪ menacing music playing]

302
00:26:30.036 --> 00:26:31.037
[Mr. Noh] Ms. Ko.

303
00:26:33.331 --> 00:26:34.540
Where are you going?

304
00:26:35.541 --> 00:26:36.751
[Seyun breathes shakily]

305
00:26:42.006 --> 00:26:43.716
[gasping]

306
00:26:45.218 --> 00:26:47.428
[yelps. straining]

307
00:26:49.681 --> 00:26:51.181
[whimpering]

308
00:26:51.182 --> 00:26:54.602
The things you go through
because of your husband…

309
00:26:56.229 --> 00:26:57.438
Am I right?

310
00:27:01.155 --> 00:27:03.407
[♪ music fades]

311
00:27:03.924 --> 00:27:06.218
LEE SUHYEONG
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

312
00:27:07.511 --> 00:27:10.013
[Suhyeong breathing heavily]

313
00:27:34.371 --> 00:27:35.372
[sighs]

314
00:27:36.206 --> 00:27:37.207
Tell me.

315
00:27:38.917 --> 00:27:40.085
Who really are you?

316
00:27:42.337 --> 00:27:43.755
Why did you come looking for me?

317
00:27:45.882 --> 00:27:46.967
Six years ago.

318
00:27:48.844 --> 00:27:50.262
my wife was abducted.

319
00:27:55.559 --> 00:27:56.977
Just like your wife.

320
00:27:58.395 --> 00:27:59.728
SUSPECT INTERROGATION REPORT

321
00:27:59.729 --> 00:28:02.815
Yuseok. I'm going to ask you
one last time.

322
00:28:02.816 --> 00:28:04.900
Where did you hide
the rest of the merchandise?

323
00:28:04.901 --> 00:28:07.403
- I don't know. How am I supposed to know?
- [phone buzzing]

324
00:28:07.404 --> 00:28:09.239
INCOMING CALL
GYEONGMIN

325
00:28:09.823 --> 00:28:13.033
If you keep playing dumb
after I come back from this call.

326
00:28:13.034 --> 00:28:14.910
you'll be dead tonight.

327
00:28:14.911 --> 00:28:16.829
Be smart about this. Geez.

328
00:28:16.830 --> 00:28:19.332
[♪ mysterious music playing]

329
00:28:20.375 --> 00:28:21.876
Hey. honey. Don't wait up.

330
00:28:21.877 --> 00:28:24.086
I don't think I can make it home today.

331
00:28:24.087 --> 00:28:25.922
[Mr. Noh] Detective Lee Suhyeong?

332
00:28:31.011 --> 00:28:32.136
Yeah. who's this?

333
00:28:32.137 --> 00:28:34.681
And why do you have my wife's phone?

334
00:28:35.557 --> 00:28:36.725
[phone buzzes]

335
00:28:39.144 --> 00:28:41.354
GYEONGMIN

336
00:28:46.776 --> 00:28:48.152
What the hell?

337
00:28:48.153 --> 00:28:49.488
Keep it down.

338
00:28:50.489 --> 00:28:54.451
If the cops around you catch on.
I'll have no choice but to kill her.

339
00:28:58.914 --> 00:29:01.040
What do you want from me?

340
00:29:01.041 --> 00:29:02.626
Thirty million won in cash.

341
00:29:03.251 --> 00:29:06.420
In one hour. meet me
at Yeongjin Industrial Complex. alone.

342
00:29:06.421 --> 00:29:07.505
[line disconnects]

343
00:29:07.506 --> 00:29:09.508
[♪ music continues]

344
00:29:21.937 --> 00:29:23.939
[phone buzzing]

345
00:29:26.274 --> 00:29:27.358
Yeah.

346
00:29:27.359 --> 00:29:28.818
[Mr. Noh]
You see the door in front of you?

347
00:29:29.486 --> 00:29:31.238
Leave the money there and walk away.

348
00:29:32.489 --> 00:29:36.408
- And my wife?
- I'll tell you where she is in 10 minutes.

349
00:29:36.409 --> 00:29:37.744
[line disconnects]

350
00:29:47.712 --> 00:29:49.838
[phone buzzing]

351
00:29:49.839 --> 00:29:52.424
[♪ music fades]

352
00:29:52.425 --> 00:29:53.593
Where is she?

353
00:29:55.303 --> 00:29:56.555
Where is my wife?

354
00:29:59.891 --> 00:30:01.017
Tell me!

355
00:30:01.685 --> 00:30:03.645
- [Gyeongmin] Honey. [gasps]
- [stammers]

356
00:30:04.354 --> 00:30:05.563
Gyeongmin.

357
00:30:05.564 --> 00:30:07.982
[♪ tense music playing]

358
00:30:07.983 --> 00:30:10.150
You're okay. right? You all right?

359
00:30:10.151 --> 00:30:11.360
I don't know.

360
00:30:11.361 --> 00:30:12.696
You're not hurt. are you?

361
00:30:13.947 --> 00:30:16.032
I'm just really dizzy.

362
00:30:17.117 --> 00:30:20.870
Honey. what's going to happen to me?

363
00:30:21.371 --> 00:30:23.872
[breathing heavily]

364
00:30:23.873 --> 00:30:25.500
You're going to be fine.

365
00:30:27.043 --> 00:30:28.628
Just give me a minute.

366
00:30:31.047 --> 00:30:32.465
I'll be right there.

367
00:30:32.966 --> 00:30:34.633
[Mr. Noh] Hey. Detective.

368
00:30:34.634 --> 00:30:38.054
I think I made a huge mistake.

369
00:30:39.347 --> 00:30:40.431
What do you mean?

370
00:30:40.432 --> 00:30:46.061
[Mr. Noh] Knowing how much you love your
wife. 30 million isn't going to cut it.

371
00:30:46.062 --> 00:30:48.397
I should have asked
for at least 100 million.

372
00:30:48.398 --> 00:30:50.400
What the hell are you talking about?

373
00:30:51.651 --> 00:30:53.068
We had an agreement.

374
00:30:53.069 --> 00:30:57.490
[Mr. Noh] Get me the additional 70 million
by 1 p.m.. 2 days from now.

375
00:30:58.366 --> 00:31:00.367
Listen. you prick.

376
00:31:00.368 --> 00:31:01.785
[Mr. Noh] Insult me all you want.

377
00:31:01.786 --> 00:31:03.829
- but after you get me the money.
- [line disconnects]

378
00:31:03.830 --> 00:31:06.333
[♪ tense music continues]

379
00:31:19.763 --> 00:31:26.060
JANUARY 31

380
00:31:26.061 --> 00:31:27.895
[♪ music stops]

381
00:31:27.896 --> 00:31:29.814
[phone buzzing]

382
00:31:31.983 --> 00:31:33.484
What took you so long?

383
00:31:33.485 --> 00:31:34.610
Where's my wife?

384
00:31:34.611 --> 00:31:36.112
[Mr. Noh] I'm sorry. Detective.

385
00:31:36.738 --> 00:31:38.822
Something urgent came up.

386
00:31:38.823 --> 00:31:40.783
Leave the money by the pavilion.

387
00:31:40.784 --> 00:31:43.410
and I'll tell you
where she is in 10 minutes.

388
00:31:43.411 --> 00:31:44.412
[line disconnects]

389
00:31:56.257 --> 00:31:58.760
[♪ tense music resumes]

390
00:32:10.855 --> 00:32:12.564
8:15 P.M.. JANUARY 31

391
00:32:12.565 --> 00:32:14.693
8:16 P.M.. JANUARY 31

392
00:32:18.405 --> 00:32:19.698
[tires squeal]

393
00:32:34.963 --> 00:32:36.965
[phone buzzing]

394
00:32:39.926 --> 00:32:42.554
Hello? What's going on here?

395
00:32:43.388 --> 00:32:45.265
I got you the money as promised.

396
00:32:46.933 --> 00:32:50.352
You should let my wife go now.

397
00:32:50.353 --> 00:32:51.562
[Mr. Noh] I know.

398
00:32:51.563 --> 00:32:53.897
I totally should let her go.

399
00:32:53.898 --> 00:32:57.736
But the thing is.
I don't think I'll be able to.

400
00:32:59.320 --> 00:33:00.905
What are you talking about?

401
00:33:02.157 --> 00:33:06.285
You asked for more money.
so I brought it for you.

402
00:33:06.286 --> 00:33:07.787
Tell me about it.

403
00:33:08.455 --> 00:33:09.956
Why are you doing this?

404
00:33:11.291 --> 00:33:13.792
What's the reason?

405
00:33:13.793 --> 00:33:18.131
Detective. do you really not know
why I'm doing this?

406
00:33:20.008 --> 00:33:22.885
You're being punished for your wrongdoing.

407
00:33:22.886 --> 00:33:24.679
I'm so sorry. sir.

408
00:33:27.098 --> 00:33:29.433
I'm down on my knees
apologizing right now.

409
00:33:29.434 --> 00:33:31.018
I'm really sorry.

410
00:33:31.019 --> 00:33:34.897
What I've done is unacceptable. I'm sorry!

411
00:33:34.898 --> 00:33:36.648
But could you please…

412
00:33:36.649 --> 00:33:40.486
Could you please let my wife go?

413
00:33:40.487 --> 00:33:41.945
I'm begging you.

414
00:33:41.946 --> 00:33:43.572
So go ahead.

415
00:33:43.573 --> 00:33:45.200
Tell me what you've done wrong.

416
00:33:48.161 --> 00:33:50.162
Why apologize when you don't know?

417
00:33:50.163 --> 00:33:51.164
Detective.

418
00:33:52.665 --> 00:33:53.833
Just know this.

419
00:33:54.834 --> 00:33:56.669
What happened to your wife

420
00:33:58.630 --> 00:34:00.215
is all on you.

421
00:34:01.841 --> 00:34:04.134
- [line disconnects]
- Sir. please.

422
00:34:04.135 --> 00:34:05.178
Hello?

423
00:34:05.804 --> 00:34:06.805
Hello?

424
00:34:07.388 --> 00:34:08.723
Sir. please!

425
00:34:09.849 --> 00:34:11.893
[breathing shakily]

426
00:34:20.109 --> 00:34:21.985
[♪ music fades]

427
00:34:21.986 --> 00:34:25.365
And I got my wife back as a lifeless body.

428
00:34:31.079 --> 00:34:32.288
So you're saying…

429
00:34:33.248 --> 00:34:34.499
Yeah. it's him.

430
00:34:35.625 --> 00:34:38.128
The same man you're hunting right now.

431
00:34:38.920 --> 00:34:41.673
Since that day.
he's all I've thought about.

432
00:34:42.423 --> 00:34:44.717
The only reason
I'm still breathing is to catch him.

433
00:34:46.261 --> 00:34:50.640
And then. one day.
I heard his voice again.

434
00:34:51.224 --> 00:34:53.726
[♪ intriguing music playing]

435
00:35:08.449 --> 00:35:10.535
[♪ music intensifies]

436
00:35:12.453 --> 00:35:13.538
[Taeju] Hello?

437
00:35:14.038 --> 00:35:16.081
[Mr. Noh] Where are you. Mr. Kang?

438
00:35:16.082 --> 00:35:19.418
[Taeju]
Oh. I'm at my in-laws' house right now.

439
00:35:19.419 --> 00:35:20.502
[Mr. Noh] In-laws?

440
00:35:20.503 --> 00:35:24.132
[Taeju] They managed to prepare the money.

441
00:35:25.550 --> 00:35:26.551
[Mr. Noh] Listen to me.

442
00:35:27.093 --> 00:35:30.263
You're going to pay
for disappointing me until the end.

443
00:35:30.805 --> 00:35:33.474
You didn't keep up
your end of the deal. boss.

444
00:35:34.017 --> 00:35:35.768
And now. your wife's going to die.

445
00:35:39.522 --> 00:35:42.691
You didn't keep up
your end of the deal. boss.

446
00:35:42.692 --> 00:35:44.318
And now. your wife's going to die.

447
00:35:44.319 --> 00:35:46.696
Hey. Kang Taeju.

448
00:35:48.072 --> 00:35:49.240
This is on you.

449
00:35:52.202 --> 00:35:53.203
Detective.

450
00:35:54.662 --> 00:35:56.122
Just know this.

451
00:35:57.457 --> 00:35:59.292
What happened to your wife

452
00:36:00.710 --> 00:36:02.337
is all on you.

453
00:36:02.921 --> 00:36:04.923
[breathing heavily]

454
00:36:07.425 --> 00:36:09.510
[Suhyeong] It was the same voice…

455
00:36:16.142 --> 00:36:18.144
The same cadence and tone…

456
00:36:20.355 --> 00:36:22.106
from six years ago.

457
00:36:29.405 --> 00:36:31.908
[♪ mysterious music playing]

458
00:36:36.371 --> 00:36:37.704
These are the internal files

459
00:36:37.705 --> 00:36:40.458
on the two cases
that bastard pulled before.

460
00:36:46.297 --> 00:36:48.716
One's the murder of my wife.

461
00:36:49.759 --> 00:36:52.262
The other is a case
we suspect he's behind.

462
00:36:53.763 --> 00:36:57.850
The Seokdong Lake kidnapping
and murder from five years ago.

463
00:37:09.904 --> 00:37:11.780
ESTIMATED TOD
37-38 HRS AFTER RANSOM CALL

464
00:37:11.781 --> 00:37:13.157
Exact same MO.

465
00:37:16.286 --> 00:37:23.251
His window for murder is
36 to 38 hours post-ransom call.

466
00:37:24.085 --> 00:37:28.463
It's already been 15 hours
since he took your wife.

467
00:37:28.464 --> 00:37:32.343
Why do you think he kidnapped her?

468
00:37:33.678 --> 00:37:34.679
Beats me.

469
00:37:35.513 --> 00:37:37.307
Who knows what this guy is thinking?

470
00:37:39.100 --> 00:37:41.102
But one thing is for sure.

471
00:37:42.603 --> 00:37:44.897
Your wife is still alive.

472
00:37:45.690 --> 00:37:47.400
Though she doesn't have much time left.

473
00:37:54.198 --> 00:37:56.284
So what do I have to do now

474
00:37:56.909 --> 00:37:58.661
to save my wife?

475
00:38:00.371 --> 00:38:01.789
First. you lure him out.

476
00:38:02.457 --> 00:38:04.459
But I don't even know where he is.

477
00:38:06.210 --> 00:38:08.046
You're going to cut him a deal.

478
00:38:09.213 --> 00:38:12.090
[news anchor] At around 10:20 p.m.
at Ilseo Industrial Complex.

479
00:38:12.091 --> 00:38:13.175
a standoff erupted

480
00:38:13.176 --> 00:38:15.260
- between police and a neurosurgeon…
- [♪ music stops]

481
00:38:15.261 --> 00:38:19.264
…suspected of orchestrating
his wife's kidnapping and murder.

482
00:38:19.265 --> 00:38:21.516
The suspect disarmed an officer…

483
00:38:21.517 --> 00:38:22.518
Mr. Kang?

484
00:38:23.895 --> 00:38:24.978
He's good.

485
00:38:24.979 --> 00:38:28.231
He may have slipped into nearby
residential or busy commercial districts.

486
00:38:28.232 --> 00:38:30.443
Citizens are urged
to exercise extreme caution.

487
00:38:40.536 --> 00:38:42.538
[breathing heavily]

488
00:38:53.132 --> 00:38:56.135
[grunts. panting]

489
00:38:58.096 --> 00:38:59.555
[sighs]

490
00:39:00.973 --> 00:39:01.974
[groans]

491
00:39:06.145 --> 00:39:07.313
[huffs]

492
00:39:28.960 --> 00:39:31.462
[♪ menacing music playing]

493
00:39:32.255 --> 00:39:33.714
TUESDAY. FEBRUARY 10
ALARM

494
00:39:35.174 --> 00:39:37.385
[alarm beeping]

495
00:40:04.954 --> 00:40:06.456
[metal clangs]

496
00:40:07.373 --> 00:40:08.583
[thuds]

497
00:40:10.918 --> 00:40:12.670
[object scraping]

498
00:40:21.721 --> 00:40:24.223
[♪ menacing music continues]

499
00:40:37.695 --> 00:40:39.655
[hammer scraping]

500
00:40:49.040 --> 00:40:50.124
[thuds]

501
00:41:01.594 --> 00:41:04.262
- [♪ music fades]
- [Mr. Noh] Hey. are you ready?

502
00:41:04.263 --> 00:41:08.141
[Seonja] Punish me. O Great Spirit.
for I have sinned.

503
00:41:08.142 --> 00:41:10.977
I vowed to serve
and follow you and you only.

504
00:41:10.978 --> 00:41:14.314
Yet. I was foolish enough
to seek another deity.

505
00:41:14.315 --> 00:41:17.317
Please punish me.
for death is the only way--

506
00:41:17.318 --> 00:41:18.528
- [yelps]
- [thuds]

507
00:41:19.278 --> 00:41:20.279
- [thuds]
- [Seyun gasps]

508
00:41:21.197 --> 00:41:22.280
[body collapses]

509
00:41:22.281 --> 00:41:23.365
No.

510
00:41:23.366 --> 00:41:26.368
- [♪ intense music playing]
- [whimpering] No.

511
00:41:26.369 --> 00:41:27.702
No!

512
00:41:27.703 --> 00:41:28.787
Stop it!

513
00:41:28.788 --> 00:41:31.456
- [door banging]
- No! Don't do it!

514
00:41:31.457 --> 00:41:33.291
Please don't do this!

515
00:41:33.292 --> 00:41:38.464
Please don't do this. please!

516
00:41:42.843 --> 00:41:43.844
Ms. Lee Seonja?

517
00:41:45.179 --> 00:41:46.514
Please say something.

518
00:41:48.307 --> 00:41:50.309
Please say something. Ms. Lee.

519
00:41:55.064 --> 00:41:56.231
Ms. Lee…

520
00:41:56.232 --> 00:41:58.650
[sobbing]

521
00:41:58.651 --> 00:42:01.278
[screams] Screw you. you sick freak!

522
00:42:01.279 --> 00:42:02.529
Just kill me!

523
00:42:02.530 --> 00:42:04.114
Kill me too!

524
00:42:04.115 --> 00:42:06.492
[screaming]

525
00:42:10.371 --> 00:42:12.373
[groans. wails]

526
00:42:15.543 --> 00:42:17.545
[sobbing]

527
00:42:22.675 --> 00:42:23.842
[♪ music stops]

528
00:42:23.843 --> 00:42:26.469
Hey. Captain.
Looking at the surveillance footage.

529
00:42:26.470 --> 00:42:28.888
it looks like after Kang
fled the industrial complex.

530
00:42:28.889 --> 00:42:32.767
he entered a nearby subway station.
got off at Shinyu Station.

531
00:42:32.768 --> 00:42:35.478
and then headed toward
the open lot right by the underpass.

532
00:42:35.479 --> 00:42:38.898
But there are no cameras
from the underpass to the lot.

533
00:42:38.899 --> 00:42:40.401
so we lost him here.

534
00:42:40.943 --> 00:42:42.819
Yeah. we're sweeping the perimeter.

535
00:42:42.820 --> 00:42:45.989
but with all the blind spots
and the outdated cameras in this area.

536
00:42:45.990 --> 00:42:48.326
we still can't lock down his exact route.

537
00:42:49.243 --> 00:42:52.163
- Go back to the footage from the station.
- Yes. sir.

538
00:42:55.583 --> 00:42:57.542
[Dosik]
He definitely went there to meet someone.

539
00:42:57.543 --> 00:43:00.379
When perps are on the run. they just run.

540
00:43:00.921 --> 00:43:02.923
They don't stop to look at maps.

541
00:43:04.425 --> 00:43:08.596
It's possible he's got another accomplice
who knows where the blind spots are.

542
00:43:09.263 --> 00:43:10.264
Another accomplice?

543
00:43:11.557 --> 00:43:14.517
Check if any
of the local residents are ex-convicts.

544
00:43:14.518 --> 00:43:16.228
They likely left together in a vehicle.

545
00:43:16.979 --> 00:43:19.856
Oh. and pull every plate captured
within a five-kilometer radius

546
00:43:19.857 --> 00:43:22.108
at this hour and run background checks.

547
00:43:22.109 --> 00:43:23.693
- [detective] Yes. sir.
- We're on it.

548
00:43:23.694 --> 00:43:25.987
Police have released
citizen footage showing

549
00:43:25.988 --> 00:43:28.698
Kang brandishing a weapon
and terrorizing bystanders.

550
00:43:28.699 --> 00:43:31.159
[student] We got to run!

551
00:43:31.160 --> 00:43:32.827
Dude. I think he's crazy.

552
00:43:32.828 --> 00:43:35.664
[news anchor] Officials say Kang is armed
and extremely unstable…

553
00:43:35.665 --> 00:43:38.249
[Dr. Ko] Geez. that damn psycho.

554
00:43:38.250 --> 00:43:40.835
He's going to burn in hell.

555
00:43:40.836 --> 00:43:43.339
[object clacking in distance]

556
00:43:49.929 --> 00:43:51.514
[sighs heavily]

557
00:43:54.517 --> 00:43:56.519
[clacking continues]

558
00:44:01.774 --> 00:44:05.403
Geez. give me a break already.

559
00:44:16.247 --> 00:44:17.915
[lock whirs. beeps]

560
00:44:19.792 --> 00:44:23.963
- [♪ tense music playing]
- [gasps] What are you…

561
00:44:24.672 --> 00:44:26.340
[Taeju] Let's step inside. Father.

562
00:44:29.719 --> 00:44:31.137
Honey. what's going on?

563
00:44:31.721 --> 00:44:32.722
Everything okay?

564
00:44:35.850 --> 00:44:39.144
Are you out of your mind?
How dare you point a gun at me!

565
00:44:39.145 --> 00:44:40.146
Step inside.

566
00:44:40.896 --> 00:44:42.314
Taeju.

567
00:44:43.315 --> 00:44:44.316
What…

568
00:44:46.694 --> 00:44:47.695
Where's Seyun?

569
00:44:49.196 --> 00:44:51.031
Where is she right now?

570
00:44:52.032 --> 00:44:53.409
Don't move. Mother.

571
00:44:54.660 --> 00:44:56.287
I can't tell you anything right now.

572
00:44:57.455 --> 00:44:58.914
What do you want then?

573
00:44:59.623 --> 00:45:02.001
Why the hell are you here with a gun?

574
00:45:03.502 --> 00:45:04.503
To pick up the money.

575
00:45:05.171 --> 00:45:06.964
What? Money?

576
00:45:07.923 --> 00:45:09.592
The three billion you have here.

577
00:45:10.509 --> 00:45:12.469
I need you to hand it over to me.

578
00:45:12.470 --> 00:45:13.971
[Suhyeong] You're going to cut him a deal.

579
00:45:14.597 --> 00:45:15.722
What?

580
00:45:15.723 --> 00:45:19.185
But before you do that. you have
to let him know you've got the money.

581
00:45:20.144 --> 00:45:24.606
"A famous doctor suspected
of kidnapping and murdering his wife

582
00:45:24.607 --> 00:45:27.943
flees questioning
and even steals from his in-laws…"

583
00:45:28.694 --> 00:45:30.779
That will definitely make the headline.

584
00:45:30.780 --> 00:45:32.280
And you have to really sell it.

585
00:45:32.281 --> 00:45:35.618
Make it look like you actually
kidnapped your own wife.

586
00:45:36.577 --> 00:45:39.997
You might have to do
more than just take the money.

587
00:45:41.499 --> 00:45:42.792
[Dr. Ko] The three billion?

588
00:45:44.126 --> 00:45:46.545
So it was about money. [scoffs]

589
00:45:47.213 --> 00:45:48.923
Now I'm getting it.

590
00:45:49.757 --> 00:45:52.968
You got close to Seyun
for money from the start. right?

591
00:45:54.261 --> 00:45:56.221
See. honey? What did I tell you?

592
00:45:56.222 --> 00:45:58.891
I kept telling you that he was bad news.

593
00:45:59.892 --> 00:46:02.143
You're finally showing your true colors.

594
00:46:02.144 --> 00:46:04.813
You kept up the act pretty well. huh?

595
00:46:04.814 --> 00:46:06.315
What a performance!

596
00:46:07.233 --> 00:46:08.525
[Seyun's mother] Taeju.

597
00:46:08.526 --> 00:46:11.778
If you want the money. let Seyun go first.

598
00:46:11.779 --> 00:46:13.780
Then I'll give you the money. All of it!

599
00:46:13.781 --> 00:46:14.824
No. Mother.

600
00:46:15.366 --> 00:46:18.034
Give me the money first.
That's the only way she'll live.

601
00:46:18.035 --> 00:46:19.203
What?

602
00:46:19.829 --> 00:46:23.706
[Dr. Ko] You greedy bastard. Rot in hell!

603
00:46:23.707 --> 00:46:27.961
Taeju. How did you end up like this?

604
00:46:27.962 --> 00:46:29.754
Is this who you really are?

605
00:46:29.755 --> 00:46:34.634
I mean. this is just…
I can't believe this is happening.

606
00:46:34.635 --> 00:46:38.471
There's no point in talking
to this subhuman garbage.

607
00:46:38.472 --> 00:46:39.557
I'm calling the cops.

608
00:46:40.599 --> 00:46:41.809
I wouldn't do that. Father!

609
00:46:43.477 --> 00:46:44.686
"Father"?

610
00:46:44.687 --> 00:46:47.647
Don't you dare call me that!

611
00:46:47.648 --> 00:46:49.817
Have you no shame at all?

612
00:46:50.734 --> 00:46:52.152
I said don't do it!

613
00:46:52.653 --> 00:46:55.072
What? You're going to shoot me?

614
00:46:55.614 --> 00:46:57.950
Go on then. Shoot me!

615
00:46:58.909 --> 00:47:00.493
Shoot me. you bastard!

616
00:47:00.494 --> 00:47:02.996
[Seyun's mother]
Oh. honey. don't. Please. just…

617
00:47:02.997 --> 00:47:05.165
- You don't have the guts. do you?
- [Seyun's mother] Please.

618
00:47:08.419 --> 00:47:09.502
[gunshot]

619
00:47:09.503 --> 00:47:10.796
[Seyun's mother exclaims]

620
00:47:13.854 --> 00:47:14.855
[exclaims]

621
00:47:16.523 --> 00:47:18.942
Stop! Taeju!

622
00:47:19.693 --> 00:47:21.778
Please stop.

623
00:47:23.488 --> 00:47:25.073
Stay exactly where you are.

624
00:47:25.574 --> 00:47:27.283
[Seyun's mother] Just take it!

625
00:47:27.284 --> 00:47:29.119
Please. just take the money!

626
00:47:29.953 --> 00:47:32.079
[♪ music continues]

627
00:47:32.080 --> 00:47:34.082
[buttons beeping]

628
00:47:41.047 --> 00:47:42.340
[Seyun's mother] Go on. take it.

629
00:47:43.300 --> 00:47:44.384
Look at you.

630
00:47:45.218 --> 00:47:47.053
What would your mother say if she saw you?

631
00:47:48.555 --> 00:47:49.889
Is this what she gets

632
00:47:49.890 --> 00:47:53.810
for breaking her back all by herself.
trying to raise you right?

633
00:47:55.312 --> 00:47:56.313
[scoffs]

634
00:47:57.147 --> 00:47:58.148
Just answer me this.

635
00:48:00.650 --> 00:48:02.152
Is Seyun still alive?

636
00:48:04.404 --> 00:48:06.406
You could at least tell us that.

637
00:48:07.282 --> 00:48:08.783
Is she still alive?

638
00:48:12.037 --> 00:48:13.872
I believe so.

639
00:48:14.664 --> 00:48:15.665
[Dr. Ko] What?

640
00:48:16.291 --> 00:48:19.336
[stammers. inhales sharply]
What do you mean?

641
00:48:21.338 --> 00:48:22.339
Huh?

642
00:48:32.807 --> 00:48:34.559
[♪ music intensifies]

643
00:49:07.759 --> 00:49:10.845
LAW ENFORCEMENT

644
00:49:11.346 --> 00:49:12.555
[♪ music stops]

645
00:49:18.103 --> 00:49:20.105
[chattering on radios]

646
00:49:33.368 --> 00:49:36.371
Did he tell you anything
when he took the money?

647
00:49:37.706 --> 00:49:39.540
He was just here for the money.

648
00:49:39.541 --> 00:49:41.459
He even opened fire inside this house.

649
00:49:41.960 --> 00:49:44.044
He was in no state
to say anything sensible.

650
00:49:44.045 --> 00:49:46.214
And where have you people been?

651
00:49:47.424 --> 00:49:50.134
Are you even trying to catch this bastard?

652
00:49:50.135 --> 00:49:51.802
Well. we're doing everything we can.

653
00:49:51.803 --> 00:49:52.804
[sighs]

654
00:49:54.639 --> 00:49:56.473
What if she dies?

655
00:49:56.474 --> 00:49:58.810
[voice breaking] What if my daughter dies?

656
00:50:00.145 --> 00:50:02.063
What will you do then?

657
00:50:04.232 --> 00:50:06.443
He said he "believed so."

658
00:50:08.194 --> 00:50:09.445
Pardon?

659
00:50:09.446 --> 00:50:12.282
My husband asked him if Seyun was alive.

660
00:50:13.116 --> 00:50:15.285
and he said. "I believe so."

661
00:50:16.161 --> 00:50:18.246
Those were his words.

662
00:50:19.873 --> 00:50:20.874
He

663
00:50:22.292 --> 00:50:23.543
"believes so"?

664
00:50:24.210 --> 00:50:26.713
[♪ intriguing music playing]

665
00:50:35.805 --> 00:50:37.223
How are you?

666
00:50:40.435 --> 00:50:43.771
[news anchor] Wanted fugitive Kang Taeju.
who fled while being questioned

667
00:50:43.772 --> 00:50:46.565
over allegations of plotting
his wife's kidnapping and murder.

668
00:50:46.566 --> 00:50:49.651
is confirmed to have broken into
his in-laws' home early this morning

669
00:50:49.652 --> 00:50:52.321
- and stolen billions of won in cash.
- [chuckles]

670
00:50:52.322 --> 00:50:54.490
Authorities say Kang fired
a stolen police weapon

671
00:50:54.491 --> 00:50:56.742
during the break-in
to threaten his parents-in-law.

672
00:50:56.743 --> 00:50:58.827
leaving the public in shock.

673
00:50:58.828 --> 00:51:00.954
[news anchor 2]
Kang Taeju. a wanted fugitive

674
00:51:00.955 --> 00:51:02.414
and a prominent local neurosurgeon…

675
00:51:02.415 --> 00:51:05.459
[doctor] Dr. Ha. did you see that?

676
00:51:05.460 --> 00:51:08.087
- [news report continues faintly]
- I knew something like this would happen.

677
00:51:08.088 --> 00:51:10.423
I told you he's crazy.
I knew he'd snap one day.

678
00:51:11.007 --> 00:51:12.425
That's not who he is.

679
00:51:13.510 --> 00:51:15.386
You're a terrible judge of character.

680
00:51:17.722 --> 00:51:19.057
Oh. look who it is.

681
00:51:19.682 --> 00:51:22.476
I heard they've been hitting it off
when he's on call.

682
00:51:22.477 --> 00:51:24.228
The rumors must be true.

683
00:51:24.229 --> 00:51:25.354
[sighs]

684
00:51:25.355 --> 00:51:26.688
He's one of a kind.

685
00:51:26.689 --> 00:51:27.690
One of a kind indeed.

686
00:51:29.067 --> 00:51:30.068
Dr. Im.

687
00:51:31.319 --> 00:51:33.195
Things are already pretty tense right now.

688
00:51:33.196 --> 00:51:35.031
Don't go starting baseless rumors.

689
00:51:36.157 --> 00:51:38.200
[chuckles] Right. okay.

690
00:51:38.201 --> 00:51:41.078
[news anchor 2] Not only did police
carelessly lose track of the suspect.

691
00:51:41.079 --> 00:51:43.622
but authorities were virtually helpless

692
00:51:43.623 --> 00:51:46.041
as he scored a firearm right
in the heart of the city

693
00:51:46.042 --> 00:51:48.294
and went on to commit
another major offense.

694
00:51:49.462 --> 00:51:51.839
I was woken up by the loud blasts.

695
00:51:51.840 --> 00:51:54.049
I thought it was fireworks.

696
00:51:54.050 --> 00:51:56.760
[news anchor 2] Citizens are expressing
absolute terror over the fact that

697
00:51:56.761 --> 00:52:00.890
a violent criminal is actively roaming
the streets while armed with a gun.

698
00:52:03.017 --> 00:52:05.353
[exhales deeply]

699
00:52:15.780 --> 00:52:17.574
You made it onto the news.

700
00:52:20.577 --> 00:52:22.245
The culprit must've seen it too.

701
00:52:24.831 --> 00:52:26.748
CHOI HYEONSU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

702
00:52:26.749 --> 00:52:29.586
[♪ mysterious music playing]

703
00:52:35.884 --> 00:52:39.387
REVEALING THE TRUTH
WITH THE POWER OF SCIENCE

704
00:52:44.642 --> 00:52:45.643
[Taeju] The NFS?

705
00:52:46.102 --> 00:52:48.479
You want me to go there? Why?

706
00:52:49.063 --> 00:52:51.191
To find the bait to lure him out.

707
00:53:00.366 --> 00:53:02.451
REQUEST FOR INVESTIGATION COOPERATION

708
00:53:02.452 --> 00:53:04.537
1. CASE NUMBER. 2026-9825
2. REQUESTED EVIDENCE

709
00:53:07.540 --> 00:53:09.542
[♪ music continues]

710
00:53:24.933 --> 00:53:28.936
Hi. I'm with Seongjin Police.
I'm here to urgently collect the evidence.

711
00:53:28.937 --> 00:53:30.939
Okay. give me a moment.

712
00:53:36.152 --> 00:53:37.362
Mmm. That's odd.

713
00:53:38.446 --> 00:53:40.531
I don't see anything in the system.

714
00:53:41.199 --> 00:53:42.282
Sorry?

715
00:53:42.283 --> 00:53:44.911
We should've received
an evidence release request first.

716
00:53:45.745 --> 00:53:46.746
Oh.

717
00:53:47.664 --> 00:53:50.792
No way. that's not possible.
We definitely sent in the form.

718
00:53:51.668 --> 00:53:53.336
Seongjin Police. right?

719
00:53:54.128 --> 00:53:57.005
Yeah. I'm with Seongjin Police.

720
00:53:57.006 --> 00:53:58.132
My name is Choi Hyeonsu.

721
00:54:14.315 --> 00:54:15.942
Hi. Chief. Are you busy?

722
00:54:16.859 --> 00:54:18.945
Yeah. I just want
to check something with you.

723
00:54:20.947 --> 00:54:23.825
Yeah. the case number is 2026-9825.

724
00:54:31.958 --> 00:54:34.460
[♪ tense music playing]

725
00:54:36.170 --> 00:54:38.630
Sir. where are you going?

726
00:54:38.631 --> 00:54:40.883
Oh. they caught that punk.

727
00:54:43.261 --> 00:54:45.638
- You're all clear.
- What?

728
00:54:46.514 --> 00:54:47.598
Your request.

729
00:54:48.516 --> 00:54:49.642
Ah. [chuckles]

730
00:54:50.184 --> 00:54:53.062
Looks like there was a hiccup
on your side of the system.

731
00:54:54.147 --> 00:54:55.355
I see.

732
00:54:55.356 --> 00:54:58.608
We still have to process it first.
but since you said it's urgent.

733
00:54:58.609 --> 00:55:00.236
I'll go grab the evidence for you.

734
00:55:01.904 --> 00:55:03.655
- How can I help you?
- [officer] Oh. hey.

735
00:55:03.656 --> 00:55:06.158
It's about case number 2026-5214.
A robbery case.

736
00:55:06.159 --> 00:55:08.076
SUHYEONG
IT'S DONE

737
00:55:08.077 --> 00:55:09.245
[associate] It's done.

738
00:55:14.667 --> 00:55:16.543
[♪ music stops]

739
00:55:16.544 --> 00:55:17.670
[lock clanks]

740
00:55:51.120 --> 00:55:52.204
Hungry. right?

741
00:55:52.205 --> 00:55:54.707
[♪ menacing music playing]

742
00:55:57.335 --> 00:55:59.253
It's about time you got hungry.

743
00:56:01.714 --> 00:56:04.926
Well. I thought you would be.
so I grabbed some food.

744
00:56:13.142 --> 00:56:14.143
Take it.

745
00:56:15.937 --> 00:56:17.438
Come on. take it.

746
00:56:18.147 --> 00:56:22.193
Oh. right. I'm so stupid.
I forgot I tied your hands up.

747
00:56:23.194 --> 00:56:24.362
What do I do about that?

748
00:56:26.489 --> 00:56:30.284
So why did you do something so stupid?
Now I want to kill you.

749
00:56:38.292 --> 00:56:40.920
Ms. Ko. Listen.

750
00:56:41.754 --> 00:56:46.134
I know exactly what you're thinking
and doing. wherever you are.

751
00:57:06.863 --> 00:57:07.864
[muffled] Right.

752
00:57:09.282 --> 00:57:10.950
Don't let the cream bun go to waste.

753
00:57:14.120 --> 00:57:15.329
Better eat it soon.

754
00:57:21.085 --> 00:57:22.460
[door closes]

755
00:57:22.461 --> 00:57:24.297
[lock clanks]

756
00:57:35.266 --> 00:57:37.768
[♪ dramatic music playing]

757
00:57:47.612 --> 00:57:48.613
[grunts]

758
00:57:49.280 --> 00:57:50.281
[Mr. Noh] Listen.

759
00:57:51.657 --> 00:57:56.120
I know exactly what you're thinking
and doing. wherever you are.

760
00:58:10.509 --> 00:58:12.929
RENOWNED NEUROSURGEON
INFILTRATES THE NFS

761
00:58:13.512 --> 00:58:16.640
What on earth is this guy doing? Geez…

762
00:58:16.641 --> 00:58:17.808
[monitor beeps]

763
00:58:34.867 --> 00:58:36.869
[♪ music intensifies]

764
00:58:46.128 --> 00:58:51.132
THE HUSBAND

765
00:58:51.133 --> 00:58:53.636
[♪ closing theme song playing]

766
00:59:31.173 --> 00:59:35.719
{\an8}It's three billion won. just as promised.
You're saying you don't want it. right?

767
00:59:35.720 --> 00:59:39.097
{\an8}[Mr. Noh] Kang Taeju. you prick. I'm going
to make sure it's slow and painful.

768
00:59:39.098 --> 00:59:42.267
{\an8}- [grunts. sobs]
- [Seyun] There's not much time.

769
00:59:42.268 --> 00:59:44.894
{\an8}[Suhyeong] Don't react to him. Just wait.

770
00:59:44.895 --> 00:59:47.064
{\an8}That's the only way
you can save your wife.

771
00:59:48.399 --> 00:59:49.983
{\an8}- No!
- [siren blares]

772
00:59:49.984 --> 00:59:51.068
{\an8}[Suhyeong] Get out of here!

773
00:59:51.902 --> 00:59:53.362
{\an8}[Mr. Noh] This is the end of our deal.

774
00:59:54.113 --> 00:59:55.990
{\an8}[Dosik] Kang Taeju. stop!

775
00:59:58.534 --> 00:59:59.617
{\an8}Don't come close!

776
00:59:59.618 --> 01:00:02.037
{\an8}[Mr. Noh] Mr. Kang. it's already over.

777
01:00:02.038 --> 01:00:03.122
{\an8}It's too late.

778
01:00:03.664 --> 01:00:05.666
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon
